               <p>MR. RICHARD ABBEY. I am a <rs id="t18270405-32-viclabel180" type="occupation">tea-dealer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-32-victim260 t18270405-32-viclabel180"></join>, and live in Pancras-lane. On the 8th of March I was in <placeName id="t18270405-32-crimeloc181">Cornhill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-32-crimeloc181" type="placeName" value="Cornhill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-32-crimeloc181" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-32-off178 t18270405-32-crimeloc181"></join>, going from 'Change - I was passing a print-ship, seeing a great many people looking at something, I stopped; an officer told me my pocket was picked; I felt, and missed my handkerchief, which I saw him take from under the prisoner's arms - I had not felt it taken.</p>
